[{"_1":2,"_3":4},"routes/lang-layout",{"_5":57},"routes/beyond-work",{"_5":6},"data",{"_7":8},"hobbies",{"_9":10,"_11":12},"section",{"_20":54,"_55":56},"topics",[13,14,15],{"_16":48,"_18":49,"_20":50,"_22":51,"_24":52,"_26":53},{"_16":38,"_18":39,"_20":40,"_22":41,"_24":42,"_26":43},{"_16":17,"_18":19,"_20":21,"_22":23,"_24":25,"_26":27},"id","side-projects","emoji","🛠️","title","Tools & Pastimes I Build","summary","Taking small everyday annoyances and coding my own fix.","body_html","<p>I love taking a small everyday problem and building my own solution for it. Here are a couple of them:</p><ul><li><b>Quem?</b> — a free, ad-free web version of the \"Who am I?\" party game I play with friends. The Play Store apps are buried in ads and paywalls, so I built my own.</li><li><b>PTAX Converter</b> — in Brazil, invoicing foreign clients means converting the amounts using a special Central Bank rate. The official site is painful to use, so I took their API and wrapped it in a nicer interface.</li></ul>","links",[28,29],{"_30":36,"_32":37,"_34":35},{"_30":31,"_32":33,"_34":35},"label","PTAX Converter","url","https://gustavorizzo.github.io/conversor-ptax-logger/","note","Free · PT-BR only","Play \"Quem?\"","https://gustavorizzo.github.io/game-quem-sou-eu/","open-source","🌱","Open Source","Building on each other's solutions so we all get better technology.","<p>I love the idea behind open source: one person's solution can become a stepping stone for someone else's problem — and that person can give back in the same way. In the end, we all benefit from more mature, more capable technology.</p><p>Right now I'm contributing to a <b>Django&nbsp;+&nbsp;HTMX</b> component library, where I've been collecting the patterns I reach for every day while building real projects.</p>",[44],{"_30":45,"_32":46,"_34":47},"django-sample-components","https://pypi.org/project/django-sample-components/","PyPI","outdoors","🥾","Adventures & Sports","Trails, peaks, volleyball, and a good game of football.","<p>I love the outdoors, and hiking is my thing 🏔️. I've climbed some of the highest peaks in Brazil and once completed a <b>250&nbsp;km</b> long-distance trek. My next big dream — one I plan to make happen soon — is to walk the <b>Camino de Santiago</b>. When I'm not on a trail, you'll find me playing volleyball 🏐 or, like any good Brazilian, soccer ⚽.</p>",[],"Beyond Work","subtitle","What I get up to away from the keyboard — and a few things I build just for fun.",{"_58":59},"lang","en"]
